You can see from [regex101][1] that the regex `^\d{6}(\d{10})$` will check if there is 16digit from start to end of the `String` (so check the length) and capture the last 10.

 - `^` : start of the String
 - `\d{6}` : first 6 digit
 - `(\d{10})` : capture 10 digit
 - `$` : end of the String

So you can use it in Java with

    String s = &quot;1234567890123456&quot;;
    Pattern p = Pattern.compile(&quot;^\\d{6}(\\d{10})$&quot;);
