For an exception to be detected by the `assertThatThrownBy` method, it must be thrown when the lambda is executed _and_ the exception must reach the assertion method. In other words: if your code already catches and swallows the exception, it will never reach the assertion. Assertions can only detect _uncaught_ exceptions, not any exception thrown anywhere.

Make sure that the exception is really thrown when executing the lambda and that it is not caught elsewhere before it bubbles up and that it can reach the assertion method.

It is for instance possible for your code to catch the exception and print its stack trace. That would explain why you are &quot;seeing the exception&quot;, but it is in fact not reaching your assertion.

